cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a framework for nonmonotonic reasoning with vague and uncertain information, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces an iterative method for answer set computation, which is related to logic programming (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper discusses the terminating conditions for a class of logic programs, which is related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with prioritized rules and rules with exceptions, which are topics in machine learning and decision making (cs.LG).
